# Copy to `.env` and fill in. Loaded by scripts/check_extractor_data_quality.py
# (and any future scripts) via python-dotenv. NEVER commit the real .env.
#
# Two auth modes are supported — pick one:
#   1. OAuth U2M (recommended)  — set HOSTNAME + HTTP_PATH only. The first run
#      opens a browser tab on the same workspace Cursor's databricks-sql MCP
#      uses, then caches the token under ~/.config/databricks-sdk-py/.
#   2. Personal Access Token    — set HOSTNAME + HTTP_PATH + TOKEN.

# Workspace URL (no protocol, no trailing slash).
DATABRICKS_SERVER_HOSTNAME=nubank-e2-general.cloud.databricks.com

# SQL Warehouse HTTP path  (REQUIRED).
#   Databricks UI -> SQL Warehouses -> <your warehouse> -> Connection details
DATABRICKS_HTTP_PATH=/sql/1.0/warehouses/79f8fd6844f0c7ce

# Optional — only set this if you prefer PAT over OAuth U2M.
#   User Settings -> Developer -> Access tokens -> Generate new token
# DATABRICKS_TOKEN=dapiXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX

# --- Google Sheets service account (for gsheets.py) ----------------------------
# Only needed for the Google Sheets transport (adjustments sheet, Content roster).
# Provide a Google *service account* key via ONE of the following (checked in
# this order). Then share the target sheet with the key's `client_email`.
# See AGENTS.md -> "Google Sheets access (gsheets.py)". NEVER commit the real key.
#
#   1) Inline JSON (entire key on one line):
# GOOGLE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_JSON={"type":"service_account",...}
#
#   2) Path to the key file (recommended):
# GOOGLE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_FILE=/absolute/path/to/service-account.json
#
#   3) Google-standard path env var:
# GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS=/absolute/path/to/service-account.json
